01:06.563 --> 01:08.827
Well, there was a real bad snowfall
just west of here.

01:08.932 --> 01:11.526
So I hear. Guess they're closing
some roads down early.

01:11.635 --> 01:13.500
Just about froze to death
in my loft last night.

01:13.604 --> 01:16.505
Global warming, they say.
World's coming to an end.

01:16.607 --> 01:17.164
Right.

01:17.274 --> 01:18.263
You want coffee?

01:18.375 --> 01:19.865
Yeah.

01:19.977 --> 01:22.741
So, if it's getting too cold
in that loft of yours...

01:22.846 --> 01:24.780
Sleep on the couch
in front of the fireplace?

01:24.882 --> 01:26.042
No.

01:26.150 --> 01:28.311
You might want to try
a few extra blankets.

01:28.419 --> 01:29.408
Oh, thanks.

01:29.586 --> 01:33.750
I don't want you and your dirty socks
lying all around my living room.

01:34.658 --> 01:35.249
Hey.

01:35.359 --> 01:35.950
Hey.

01:36.126 --> 01:37.286
Scott's gotten some calls

01:37.394 --> 01:39.089
about some wild horses
up in the foothills.

01:39.196 --> 01:41.494
Just about starved.
There's a herd up near Fish Creek.

01:41.598 --> 01:42.895
Up near the fishing cabin?

01:43.400 --> 01:44.890
Yeah. There's some colts, too.

01:45.002 --> 01:47.402
- Colts?
- Oh, don't tell her that.

01:47.504 --> 01:49.904
Snow's gotten so deep, they can't
get to the grass underneath.

01:53.077 --> 01:55.102
If you start feeding them,
they just get all dependent.

01:55.212 --> 01:57.476
It's hard to be dependent
when you starve to death first.

01:57.581 --> 01:59.208
Listen.

01:59.316 --> 02:01.614
It's just not good for them
in the long run.

02:01.718 --> 02:03.982
Dying's not good for them either
in the long run.

02:04.088 --> 02:05.316
See what you started?

02:05.422 --> 02:06.684
I'm sorry. I was just saying.

02:06.790 --> 02:08.257
Well, quit saying and start working

02:08.358 --> 02:11.020
before we're up to our eyeballs
in snow here, too.

02:15.032 --> 02:16.294
Dad.

02:16.967 --> 02:19.197
- Hey.
- Hi.

02:19.937 --> 02:21.336
I just came from the bakery,

02:21.438 --> 02:23.167
and I got the most amazing
butter tarts.

02:23.273 --> 02:25.002
- Want one?
- No, thanks, hon.

02:25.109 --> 02:26.041
Okay. What's the matter?

02:26.143 --> 02:27.667
I spent the last hour in the bank

02:27.778 --> 02:30.008
explaining away
my cash-flow problems.

02:30.114 --> 02:32.480
Not to mention
the huge tax bill I got to pay.

02:32.883 --> 02:34.282
I'm sorry, Dad.

02:34.384 --> 02:36.944
Well, it'll get better.

02:37.054 --> 02:38.885
I may not have
a cattle business anymore,

02:38.954 --> 02:40.585
but at least we still have
the dude ranch.

02:40.724 --> 02:42.248
Yes. And it's doing well.

02:42.359 --> 02:44.827
So, if you need anything,
you just say the word, okay?

02:44.928 --> 02:46.896
- Thanks, honey.
- Okay.

02:48.398 --> 02:51.162
There's that oil guy,
that P.W. Morris.

02:51.268 --> 02:53.566
P.W. What kind of idiot
goes by his initials?

02:53.670 --> 02:55.661
I'm surprised that guy
shows his face in this town.

02:55.772 --> 02:58.002
Yeah. You know what?
I got to run, Dad, okay?

02:58.108 --> 02:59.507
- I'll see you.
- Okay, honey.

03:08.919 --> 03:12.514
Hey, boy.
How you doing?

03:13.590 --> 03:14.716
Hey.

03:15.325 --> 03:18.419
Grandpa? That whole attitude
drives me crazy.

03:18.529 --> 03:21.396
- I think we should do something.
- Yeah, but...

03:21.532 --> 03:24.134
I have a plan.

03:24.134 --> 03:25.761
Of course you do.

03:27.738 --> 03:29.899
I was thinking maybe a road trip.

03:30.774 --> 03:32.071
- Road trip?
- Yeah.

03:32.176 --> 03:33.438
Just you and me.

03:33.977 --> 03:34.909
I'm listening.

03:35.012 --> 03:36.980
Maybe we could take your truck
with a big load of hay

03:37.080 --> 03:39.605
up to Fish Creek,
you know, on Saturday.

03:39.716 --> 03:41.741
Up to Grandpa's fishing cabin.

03:41.852 --> 03:45.288
And feed the wild horses.

03:47.925 --> 03:48.983
Sounds okay to me.

03:49.092 --> 03:51.754
But I don't think Jack's gonna think
it's such a good idea.

03:51.862 --> 03:54.092
Maybe Grandpa
doesn't need to know.

04:13.517 --> 04:15.917
♪ <i>And at the break of day</i> ♪

04:16.019 --> 04:20.422
♪ <i>You sank into your dream</i> ♪

04:20.524 --> 04:24.551
♪ <i>You dreamer</i> ♪

04:24.661 --> 04:27.095
♪ <i>You dreamer</i> ♪

04:28.832 --> 04:34.099
♪ <i>You dreamer</i> ♪

04:34.199 --> 04:39.199
